parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause various malfunctions, including loss of power, stalling, and failure to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
stalls while driving
experiences intermittent electrical issues
and has malfunctioning accessories such as wipers
lights
and locks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system failure can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is illuminated on the dashboard
and the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and failure to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift gears
stalls while driving
and experiences intermittent transmission issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to fail to start, stall while driving, or experience intermittent electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
stalls while driving
and experiences intermittent electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when braking
vibration in the steering wheel or brake pedal
difficulty stopping
and uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake master cylinder failure can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal sticks to the floor
delayed return of brake pedal to its normal position
and sudden loss of brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake hydraulic system failure can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal sticks to the floor
delayed return of brake pedal to its normal position
and sudden loss of brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or shakes while shifting
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine RPMs rev up or down unexpectedly
the transmission shifts erratically
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the battery drains or dies
the starter motor fails
the vehicle's accessories (e.g. windows
locks
signals) malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transfer case makes an abnormal noise
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transfer case leaks fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
